        <p style="font-size: 36px;font-weight:bold">Our Commitment</p>
        <p>BAYADA is committed to creating a culture and environment of diversity, equity, and inclusion (DEI) where
            all employees can thrive and all clients can receive high-quality, personalized care with a sense of
            well-being, dignity, and trust. </p>
        <p><span style="font-weight:bold">Diversity</span> reflects the ways people are different from one another.
            This goes beyond the boundaries of race and gender to include culture, age, sexual orientation,
            ethnicity, socio-economic background, religion, neurodiversity, gender identity, experiences,
            disability, and invisible illness.  </p>
        <p><span style="font-weight:bold">Equity</span> creates fair treatment, access, opportunity, and advancement
            for individuals by establishing systems and processes that counteract social inequities and prevent the
            formation of barriers.   </p>
        <p><span style="font-weight:bold">Inclusion</span> fosters an environment where individuals feel safe to
            engage and participate fully because they feel respected, free to express their ideas, and valued for
            their unique voice, perspective, and abilities. </p>
        <p>While <a href="https://www.bayada.com/the-bayada-way.asp" target="_blank"
                style="font-style:italic;">The BAYADA Way</a>
            always has been aligned with DEI values, our intentional journey as an organization <a
                onclick="document.getElementById('standing-together').scrollIntoView();">began in 2020</a> to
            learn more, do better, and ensure that DEI principles are embedded throughout our business practices and
            strategic goals. In partnership and consultation with <a href="https://thediversitymovement.com/"
                target="_blank">The Diversity Movement</a>, BAYADA began by learning, listening, sharing, and
            organizing. </p>
        <p style="font-size: 25px;font-weight:bold">Learning </p>
        <ul style="list-style: disc;">
            <li style="margin-left:25px;font-size: 22px;">Offering the foundational <span
                    style="font-style: italic;">Diversity: Beyond the Checkbox</span>
                courses to directors and office employees </li>
            <li style="margin-left:25px;font-size: 22px;">Created a DEI portal where all employees can access a wide
                variety of lifelong learning resources </li>
        </ul>
        <p style="font-size: 25px;font-weight:bold">Listening</p>
        <ul style="list-style: disc;">
            <li style="margin-left:25px;font-size: 22px;">Completed 26+ hours of listening sessions with employees
                throughout the organization </li>
            <li style="margin-left:25px;font-size: 22px;">Adopted the <a href="https://www.thoughtexchange.com/"
                    target="_blank">ThoughtExchange</a> real-time discussion platform
                for ongoing DEI surveys, collaboration, engagement, and growth at all levels </li>
        </ul>
        <p style="font-size: 25px;font-weight:bold">Sharing</p>
        <ul style="list-style: disc;">
            <li style="margin-left:25px;font-size: 22px;">Began hosting monthly DEI discussion webcasts with the CEO
                and a panel of employees from all levels of the organization, with live comments and Q&A from
                viewers </li>
            <li style="margin-left:25px;font-size: 22px;">Began reporting and discussing DEI progress in monthly
                executive leadership meetings, quarterly board of trustees meetings, and quarterly directors
                meetings </li>
            <li style="margin-left:25px;font-size: 22px;">Incorporated DEI topics into weekly companywide <span style="font-style: italic;">The BAYADA
                Way</span> “Key Action of the Week” small-team discussions and exercises </li>
        </ul>
        <p style="font-size: 25px;font-weight:bold">Organizing</p>
        <ul  style="list-style: disc;">
            <li style="margin-left:25px;font-size: 22px;">Established the Office of Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion
            </li>
            <li style="margin-left:25px;font-size: 22px;">Established three Employee Resource Councils:
                BAYADA Pride (LGBTQIA+), R.E.D. (Racial/Ethnic Diversity), and W.I.L.L. (Women in Limitless
                Leadership) </li>
            <li  style="margin-left:25px;font-size: 22px;">Updated our holiday policy to be more flexible and
                inclusive </li>
            <li style="margin-left:25px;font-size: 22px;">Revisited procurement decisions regarding medical
                supplies, now providing options including clear masks and multiple skin tone bandages </li>
            <li style="margin-left:25px;font-size: 22px;">Added DEI learning and practices into recruiting,
                onboarding, and career advancement programs </li>

        </ul>
        <p>Together, we are building the skills and understanding required to be more effective allies to each other
            and to people in our communities who deserve equitable access to best-in-class health care. </p>
